@NODE E.mnote "MultiView note"


This guide uses 8 colours, here and in the @{"Examples" LINK E.examp} and
@{"Hints" LINK E.hints} sections. It will be best displayed if MultiView opens
its window on a 8-colour (or higher-colour) Workbench or if you use a Screen
Manager to force explicitly MultiView to open its own screen with depth 3 (or
higher).


@{FG FILLTEXT}If this sentence and the previous one are displayed in the same
colour, MultiView (or your equivalent program) now displays text in 4 colours
only!@{FG TEXT}

